<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="UnnecessaryFinalModifierSniff.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PHP/CodeSniffer/Standards/Generic/Sniffs/CodeAnalysis/UnnecessaryFinalModifierSniff.php"><scope doc="Detects unnecessary final modifiers inside of final classes.&#10;&#10;This rule is based on the PMD rule catalog. The Unnecessary Final Modifier&#10;sniff detects the use of the final modifier inside of a final class which&#10;is unnecessary.&#10;&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;final class Foo&#10;{&#10;    public final function bar()&#10;    {&#10;    }&#10;}&#10;&lt;/code&gt;&#10;&#10;@category  PHP&#10;@package   PHP_CodeSniffer&#10;@author    Manuel Pichler &lt;mapi@manuel-pichler.de&gt;&#10;@copyright 2007-2008 Manuel Pichler. All rights reserved.&#10;@license   http://www.opensource.org/licenses/bsd-license.php BSD License&#10;@version   Release: 1.4.6&#10;@link      http://pear.php.net/package/PHP_CodeSniffer" ilk="class" interfacerefs="PHP_CodeSniffer_Sniff" line="40" lineend="96" name="Generic_Sniffs_CodeAnalysis_UnnecessaryFinalModifierSniff"><scope attributes="public" doc="Registers the tokens that this sniff wants to listen for.&#10;&#10;@return array(integer)" ilk="function" line="49" lineend="53" name="register" returns="array" signature="array register()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Processes this test, when one of its tokens is encountered.&#10;&#10;@param PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile The file being scanned.&#10;@param int                  $stackPtr  The position of the current token&#10;                                       in the stack passed in $tokens.&#10;&#10;@return void" ilk="function" line="65" lineend="93" name="process" signature="void process(PHP_CodeSniffer_File $phpcsFile, int $stackPtr)"><variable citdl="PHP_CodeSniffer_File" ilk="argument" line="65" name="phpcsFile" /><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="65" name="stackPtr" /><variable line="83" name="next" /><variable citdl="tokens" line="68" name="token" /><variable citdl="phpc